  "text": "The changes of macroscopic properties induced by the gold ions irradiation can be compared with the recent results obtained by Karakurt with 7 MeV Au ions irradiation [CITATION_1] which showed a decrease of hardness of similar amplitude, −38% compared to −36% in our study, and a decrease of density that seems to be higher, −2.7% compared to −1.6% in this study. Nevertheless, the density change measured by Karakurt should thus be corrected due to the lower ion range estimation by SRIM simulation. By taking the ion range correction factor of 1.4 ( Fig. 1) , the density change from Karakurt study is thus of around 1.9% which is closer to the value we obtained. Therefore, it shows the importance of the range measurement of the implanted ions to evaluate the density changes under external irradiation, and the need to measure the electronic energy loss of heavy ions in a light matrix so as to correct the data-base used by SRIM. The accurate simulation of material transformation under external irradiation would be improved by such measurements.",
